article.headline: Cent. Arkansas 24, Glenville St. 10
article.story: CONWAY, Ark. -- Robbie Park threw for a career-high 358 yards and Central Arkansas beat Glenville State 24-10 Saturday night. Park was 25-for-33 passing and found T.J. Adams on a 22-yard touchdown pass for the Bears (2-1). Brent Grimes scored on a 3-yard run, and Leonard Ceaser added a TD on a 1-yard plunge. LeAndre Johnson rushed for 60 yards and gave the Pioneers (2-3) their only TD of the night, scoring on a 7-yard run in the game's final three minutes. Glenville State quarterback Jaes McCants was 17-for-31 passing for 224 yards.
